snippet.textDisplay: Just came across this track, The poetry is Genesis with Baba Bulleh Shah - and the entire 'Discography' of HUMAN beings - in its very own essence. The contrast of Ying Yang, the lail o nahar, the masculine-feminine, sun & moon...everything around us, is built upon that 'ethos'. I like the production of the soundtrack, the rhythm pronounces Earth whilst the lyrical flow is water, the flute is that higher frequency bird's eye view, with the passion, is fire...and the language is the HEART. it is our cosmos, with dark settings representing the space, with each room being an epoch, with plenty of rooms empty - God says, Roam the earth and see how many nations were destroyed, it just those who believe are the real torch bearers - just like our stars at the night sky...
